                  <persName id="t18300415-129-person1204">
                  MARY 
                  ANN FOX
               <interp inst="t18300415-129-person1204" type="surname" value="ANN FOX"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-129-person1204" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-129-person1204" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the wife of John Fox. On the 24th of March I took his watch to pawn in <placeName id="t18300415-129-crimeloc728">Gilbert-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-129-crimeloc728" type="placeName" value="Gilbert-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300415-129-crimeloc728" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300415-129-off726 t18300415-129-crimeloc728"></join>; a young man looked at it, and gave it to another, who laid it on the counter - the prisoner and another young man were in the box; the prisoner snatched it up, and ran away with it - I had never seen him before; I saw him about ten minutes at that time - I am quite sure he is the man; the watch was brought to me the next morning.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-129-person1205">
                  ROBERT 
                  MUNKITRICK
               <interp inst="t18300415-129-person1205" type="surname" value="MUNKITRICK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-129-person1205" type="given" value="ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300415-129-person1205" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Police-officer. On the 25th of March, at night, I was on duty, and found the prisoner in Parker-row, Deptford-road, in bed - I found the watch there; he told me he took it from a lark, and meant to take it back the next morning.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>The prisoner put in a written Defence, stating that he intended to return the watch to the prosecutrix, who had previously sold him a duplicate and knew him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300415-129-person1206">
